(155,	1,	'2017-06-09 11:18:16',	'2017-06-09 08:18:16',	'Research and Survey Institute GEOTECH took part at the 8th International Workshop on Advanced Ground Penetrating Radar - IWAGPR 2015, which was held in Florence, Italy, from the 7th to 10th of July, 2015. Geophysicist of our company presented the paper «Computer-Aided Data Processing for GPR Profiling Applications» and new Construction Scan 1700 3D. All papers presented at the conference will be published in the workshop proceedings.\r\n\r\nTopics of IWAGPR 2015 included novel developments of GPR systems and antennas, advanced data processing algorithms for improved subsurface imaging, radar data modelling approaches and inversion strategies for qualitative and quantitative reconstruction of soil and material properties, and finally, data interpretation in a range of fields, including geology and sedimentology, glaciology, environmental and agricultural engineering (e.g., hydrological monitoring, digital soil mapping, forestry), civil engineering (e.g., utility detection, monitoring of transport infrastructures, non-destructive testing),  UXOs and landmines detection, archaeology and cultural heritage, among others. \r\n\r\nFor more information refer to Conference Program.',	'IWAGPR 2015',	'',	'publish',	'closed',	'closed',	'',	'iwagpr-2015',	'',	'',	'2017-06-09 12:50:17',	'2017-06-09 09:50:17',	'',	0,	'http://geotech.3331141.xeovo.ml/?post_type=news&#038;p=155',	0,	'news',	'',	0),
